# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AI Grader configuration. Copy to `.env` and fill in.
# Read by the Rust backend at runtime (see src-tauri/src/config.rs).
# The .env file is gitignored — never commit real values.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Remote licensing gatekeeper (Google Cloud Function).
# Validates the activation code + heartbeat pulses, and returns the Gemini API
# key as `access_token`. The app keeps that key in RAM only.
AIGRADER_LICENSE_ENDPOINT="https://REGION-PROJECT.cloudfunctions.net/license-gateway"

# Gemini model id (AI Studio / Generative Language API).
AIGRADER_MODEL="gemini-2.5-pro"

# Heartbeat cadence (hours) and grace window (days). Defaults match the spec.
AIGRADER_HEARTBEAT_HOURS="24"
AIGRADER_GRACE_DAYS="7"

# ── DEV ONLY ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# If set, the app injects this Gemini API key into RAM at boot and marks itself
# activated, so you can test grading WITHOUT the Cloud Function. Leave blank in
# production — the key should come from the licensing gateway instead.
AIGRADER_DEV_API_KEY=""
